{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A\n    \n      Modular Monolith ★ RECOMMENDED\n      Single ASP.NET MVC app with feature-based module folders (Games, Admin, Blog, Users, Scraper). Scraper runs as an IHostedService + Quartz.NET inside the same process. Supabase handles auth & file storage; EF Core + PostgreSQL owns all domain data.\n      \n        \n          Pros\n          \n            One codebase, one Docker image\n            Simple local dev — just dotnet run\n            Modules share DB transaction context\n            Easy to extract later if needed\n            Quartz.NET gives persistent job scheduling\n          \n        \n        \n          Cons\n          \n            Scraper failures could impact web requests (mitigated by background service isolation)\n            Scaling web and scraper together (not separately)","choice":"a","id":null,"timestamp":1776652465953}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A\n    \n      Modular Monolith ★ RECOMMENDED\n      Single ASP.NET MVC app with feature-based module folders (Games, Admin, Blog, Users, Scraper). Scraper runs as an IHostedService + Quartz.NET inside the same process. Supabase handles auth & file storage; EF Core + PostgreSQL owns all domain data.\n      \n        \n          Pros\n          \n            One codebase, one Docker image\n            Simple local dev — just dotnet run\n            Modules share DB transaction context\n            Easy to extract later if needed\n            Quartz.NET gives persistent job scheduling\n          \n        \n        \n          Cons\n          \n            Scraper failures could impact web requests (mitigated by background service isolation)\n            Scaling web and scraper together (not separately)","choice":"a","id":null,"timestamp":1776652468821}
